cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR

This paper involves computer vision and machine learning techniques for automated tree detection and species recognition using publicly available aerial and street view images of Google Maps. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves supervised classification and convolutional neural networks, which are common in the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with tracking trees over time, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques for recognizing changes in individual trees, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
